# Dhamma App — example environment variables.
# Copy to `.env.local` and fill in only if you choose to attach a real provider.
# The MVP ships WITHOUT any external LLM dependency; askDhamma() defaults to a
# local, fail-closed, source-grounded extractive RAG.

# Optional: enable a real LLM provider in the Ask path (unset = local mode).
# DHAMMA_LLM_PROVIDER=openai

# Optional: provider credentials. NEVER commit real values.
# OPENAI_API_KEY=

# --- Trusted corpus asset origin (server-only, never NEXT_PUBLIC) ---
# These resolve the origin used to self-fetch the immutable /corpus/* Pali and
# translation shards. They are NEVER derived from Host / X-Forwarded-Host /
# X-Forwarded-Proto. Priority:
#   1. VERCEL_PROJECT_PRODUCTION_URL - the stable production apex that serves
#      the static corpus assets (e.g. https://dhamma-tau.vercel.app). Vercel
#      injects this automatically in production.
#   2. VERCEL_URL - the exact deployment URL of the running function. Vercel
#      injects this automatically in preview.
#   3. local fallback - http://127.0.0.1:<PORT> (PORT default 3000).
# Both Vercel values must be https *.vercel.app with no embedded credentials.
# VERCEL_PROJECT_PRODUCTION_URL=https://your-project.vercel.app
# VERCEL_URL=your-deployment.vercel.app
# PORT=3000
